3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper provides an analytical characterization of all possible values of personalized PageRank for any node, which could be of interest to researchers working on algorithms for analyzing network structures. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of personalized PageRank for analyzing complex networks, which could be relevant to researchers working on control and optimization of networked systems. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents new theoretical results on personalized PageRank, which could be relevant to researchers working on computational methods for analyzing complex systems in various fields.
